HEADWORD: Trfl
<hw>Tr⟦eacute⟧`fl⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>tr⟦eacute⟧fl⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Trefoil</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having a three-lobed extremity or extremities, as
a cross; also, more rarely, ornamented with trefoils projecting from the
edges, as a bearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

